  "prompt": "Why do you like asking questions on Quora instead of searching on google?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why someone might prefer asking questions on Quora instead of searching on Google:\n\n1. **Personalized Responses**: Quora allows users to ask specific questions and receive personalized answers from real people who may have relevant expertise or experience.\n\n2. **Community Insight**: On Quora, the answers often reflect the insights and experiences of a community of individuals, providing a range of perspectives that may not be found through a simple Google search.\n\n3. **Interactive**: Users can further engage with respondents by asking follow-up questions, seeking clarification, or discussing the topic in more detail.\n\n4. **Quality Control**: Answers on Quora can be upvoted or downvoted by the community, which can help highlight more accurate or helpful responses.\n\n5. **Discovery of Related Topics**: Browsing through answers can lead to discovering related questions and topics that you might not have initially considered.\n\n6. **Expert Opinions**: Quora has many subject matter experts from various fields who provide in-depth answers, offering expertise that might be harder to find through general search results.\n\nUltimately, the choice between using Google and asking on Quora depends on the nature of the inquiry and personal preference for the type of information and interaction desired.",
